text = "[center][b]How To Play[/b][/center]\n\n[b]Core Loop[/b]\n- Start in combat, then choose rooms on the map.\n- In combat, play cards to shape a volley, then launch.\n- Clear all bricks to earn rewards and gold.\n\n[b]Combat Flow[/b]\n- Each turn you draw 4 cards (max hand size 7) and get energy.\n- Threat is the damage you take when a ball is lost or you end the turn.\n- Click the deck stack to view your deck contents.\n\n[b]Block Attributes[/b]\n- Shielded sides: visible as shield strips on the block.\n- Regenerating: shown with a â†» icon and gains HP when a ball drops.\n- Cursed: shown with a ðŸ—¡ icon; destroying it adds a Wound to your deck.\n\n[b]Cards[/b]\n- Punch (1): +1 volley damage.\n- Twin Launch (1): Gain one extra launch this volley.\n- Guard (1): Gain 5 block.\n- Widen Paddle (1): Widen paddle for 2 turns.\n- Bomb (2): Destroy up to 3 random bricks.\n- MOAB (3): Destroy up to 10 random bricks. (Unlock: Play Bomb 5 times.)\n- Parry (1): Block the next Wound gained this volley.\n- Riposte (1): If you have a Parry in hand, discard it to block a Wound and destroy a random brick. (Unlock: Play Parry 10 times.)\n- Rally (0): Draw 2 cards.\n- Focus (1): +1 energy this turn.\n- Haste (1): Paddle moves faster for 2 turns.\n- Stasis (1): Slow balls this volley.\n- Wound (1): Play to remove it from your deck.\n- What Doesn't Kill Us (1): If you have a Wound in hand, remove it and gain 2 energy. (Unlock: Play Wound 10 times.)\n\n[b]Buffs (Run-Specific)[/b]\n- Upgrade starting hand (+1).\n- Vitality: +10 max HP and heal 10.\n\n[b]Ball Mods (Run-Specific)[/b]\n- Explosives: Explode bricks on hit.\n- Spikes: Ignore shielded sides on hit.\n- Miracle: One floor bounce per use.\n- Persist checkbox keeps your selected mod active while charges remain.\n\n[b]Controls[/b]\n- Move paddle: Arrow keys or A/D\n- Slow move: Hold Ctrl\n- Launch: Space\n- End Turn: Tab\n- Quit: Esc\n"

